CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 2, 1957, pg. A13 reads: "Kappa Silhouettes - This charming group, composed of wives of members of Kappa Alpha Psi Fraternity, call themselves "Kappa Silhouettes." They sponsored one of the season's top social events, a black and white ball, at Union Hall last Friday night.  Seated, left to right: Mrs. Ione Johnson, president, Mrs. Ann Barnett and MRs. Rose Willis.  Standing: Mmes. Marian Smith, Ruth Greenlee, Estelle Hill, Helen Evans, Gloria Mungin, Helen Hailstork, Alma Davis and Ethel Holland. - Teenie Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of eleven Kappa Silhouette members, seated, left to right: Ione Johnson, Ann Barnett, and Rose Willis; standing, left to right: Marian Smith, Ruth Greenlee, Estelle Hill, Helen Evans, Gloria Mungin, Helen Hailstork, Alma Davis ,and Ethel Holland, posed in Union Hall for Black and White Ball
